Exclude the first letter of each word using the `slice` method. Then, add the remaining letters to a new list called `result`. Return that list when your function finishes.

***Note:*** make sure you start with an empty list and append items onto it as you iterate through words. Otherwise, you will overwrite what you have appended previously. You can do this by using a variable name like `my_list` instead of the function `list`.
'''
def keep_only_names(words):
    result = []

    for word in words:
        if word[0].isupper():
            result.append(word)

    return result
